---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Buyers stopped searching. They started asking. | AquiferGrowth GEO"
  description="Generative Engine Optimization for ecommerce brands. Get named in ChatGPT, Perplexity, Claude, Gemini, and Google AI Overviews when your buyer asks."
>
  <Header />
  <main>

    <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
    <!-- HERO                                        -->
    <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
    <section class="geo-hero">
      <div class="geo-hero__bg-blur"></div>
      <div class="geo-hero__bg-blur geo-hero__bg-blur--right"></div>
      <div class="geo-hero__inner container">
        <div class="geo-hero__copy">
          <span class="geo-hero__eyebrow">AI Optimization &middot; GEO</span>
          <h1 class="geo-hero__title">
            Buyers stopped searching.<br />
            <span class="text-gradient">They started asking.</span>
          </h1>
          <p class="geo-hero__subtitle">
            When your buyer asks ChatGPT, Perplexity, Claude, or Google's AI Overview who to buy from &mdash; you either get named or you don't. We measure it in <b class="geo-hero__kbd">% of responses</b> and we grow it.
          </p>
          <div class="geo-hero__cta-row">
            <a href="/contact" class="geo-btn">
              <span>Let's Chat</span>
              <span class="geo-animated-dots"><span></span><span></span><span></span></span>
            </a>
            <a href="#playbook" class="geo-hero__link">See the playbook &rarr;</a>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Mini answer-engine mock -->
        <div class="geo-hero__mock" aria-hidden="true">
          <div class="geo-mock">
            <div class="geo-mock__bar">
              <span class="geo-mock__dot"></span>
              <span class="geo-mock__dot"></span>
              <span class="geo-mock__dot"></span>
              <span class="geo-mock__url">chat.openai.com</span>
            </div>
            <div class="geo-mock__body">
              <div class="geo-mock__q">
                <span class="geo-mock__q-label">You</span>
                <p>What's the best hydration stick for adrenal support?</p>
              </div>
              <div class="geo-mock__a">
                <span class="geo-mock__a-label">
                  <svg viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M10 2l2.4 5.2 5.6.6-4.2 3.9 1.2 5.5L10 14.6 4.98 17.2l1.24-5.5L2 7.8l5.6-.6L10 2z"/></svg>
                  ChatGPT
                </span>
                <p>A few brands worth looking at:</p>
                <ul>
                  <li><b class="geo-mock__brand">Minerals &amp; Chill</b> <em>(cited)</em></li>
                  <li>Competitor B</li>
                  <li>Competitor C</li>
                </ul>
                <p class="geo-mock__cite">Sources: livehealthillie.com &middot; reddit.com &middot; muscleandfitness.com</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
    <!-- 02 · THE SHIFT                              -->
    <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
    <section class="geo-section">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="geo-sheet">
          <div class="geo-intro">
            <span class="geo-eyebrow">The shift</span>
            <h2 class="geo-section__title">Search moved. Nobody told your <span class="text-gradient">funnel</span>.</h2>
            <p class="geo-section__subtitle">Four shifts are already draining top of funnel. Most brands haven't noticed &mdash; because dashboards don't measure &ldquo;didn't get mentioned.&rdquo;</p>
          </div>

          <div class="geo-args">
            <!-- 01: You aren't in the answer -->
            <article class="geo-arg">
              <div class="geo-arg__viz">
                <div class="geo-viz-answer">
                  <div class="geo-viz-answer__q">Best magnesium stick for stress?</div>
                  <div class="geo-viz-answer__list">
                    <div class="geo-viz-answer__row">1. Brand A</div>
                    <div class="geo-viz-answer__row">2. Brand B</div>
                    <div class="geo-viz-answer__row">3. Brand C</div>
                    <div class="geo-viz-answer__row geo-viz-answer__row--you">
                      <span>&larr;</span> You: not mentioned
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="geo-arg__body">
                <div class="geo-arg__num">01</div>
                <h3 class="geo-arg__title">You aren't in the answer.</h3>
                <p class="geo-arg__copy">The buyer asks a question. Three brands get named. You are not one of them. There is no page 2. There is no scroll. The buyer moves on.</p>
              </div>
            </article>

            <!-- 02: SEO clicks shrinking -->
            <article class="geo-arg">
              <div class="geo-arg__viz">
                <div class="geo-viz-chart">
                  <div class="geo-viz-chart__label">Organic clicks &middot; 12 mo</div>
                  <svg viewBox="0 0 200 90" class="geo-viz-chart__svg" aria-hidden="true">
                    <defs>
                      <linearGradient id="geoDown" x1="0" y1="0" x2="0" y2="1">
                        <stop offset="0%" stop-color="#FF4D6D" stop-opacity="0.45" />
                        <stop offset="100%" stop-color="#FF4D6D" stop-opacity="0" />
                      </linearGradient>
                    </defs>
                    <path d="M0,20 L30,26 L60,32 L90,44 L120,58 L150,68 L180,76 L200,82 L200,90 L0,90 Z" fill="url(#geoDown)" />
                    <path d="M0,20 L30,26 L60,32 L90,44 L120,58 L150,68 L180,76 L200,82" stroke="#FF4D6D" stroke-width="2" fill="none" />
                    <circle cx="200" cy="82" r="3" fill="#FF4D6D" />
                  </svg>
                  <div class="geo-viz-chart__badge">
                    <span class="geo-viz-chart__badge-dot"></span>
                    AI Overview took the click
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="geo-arg__body">
                <div class="geo-arg__num">02</div>
                <h3 class="geo-arg__title">SEO clicks are shrinking.</h3>
                <p class="geo-arg__copy">Google's AI Overview answers the question at the top &mdash; and the buyer never clicks. Same query, same intent, half the traffic. That's the new baseline.</p>
              </div>
            </article>

            <!-- 03: AI reads structure, not vibes -->
            <article class="geo-arg">
              <div class="geo-arg__viz">
                <div class="geo-viz-code">
                  <div class="geo-viz-code__row geo-viz-code__row--bad">
                    <span class="geo-viz-code__mark">&times;</span>
                    <code>&lt;div class="product-hero"&gt;</code>
                  </div>
                  <div class="geo-viz-code__row geo-viz-code__row--bad">
                    <span class="geo-viz-code__mark">&times;</span>
                    <code>&lt;h1&gt;Buy Now&lt;/h1&gt;</code>
                  </div>
                  <div class="geo-viz-code__row geo-viz-code__row--bad">
                    <span class="geo-viz-code__mark">&times;</span>
                    <code>Reviews: 4.8 stars ()</code>
                  </div>
                  <div class="geo-viz-code__row geo-viz-code__row--good">
                    <span class="geo-viz-code__mark">&check;</span>
                    <code>&lt;script type="application/ld+json"&gt;</code>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="geo-arg__body">
                <div class="geo-arg__num">03</div>
                <h3 class="geo-arg__title">AI reads structure, not vibes.</h3>
                <p class="geo-arg__copy">LLMs parse the page. If your specs, price, reviews, and answers aren't marked up as structured data &mdash; they don't exist. Nice copy alone doesn't cite.</p>
              </div>
            </article>

            <!-- 04: Cited out of context -->
            <article class="geo-arg">
              <div class="geo-arg__viz">
                <div class="geo-viz-sources">
                  <div class="geo-viz-sources__label">You're being cited from:</div>
                  <div class="geo-viz-sources__row">
                    <span class="geo-viz-sources__ic">r/</span>
                    <span>reddit.com/r/supplements</span>
                    <span class="geo-viz-sources__tag geo-viz-sources__tag--warn">2019</span>
                  </div>
                  <div class="geo-viz-sources__row">
                    <span class="geo-viz-sources__ic">tp</span>
                    <span>trustpilot.com/reviews</span>
                    <span class="geo-viz-sources__tag geo-viz-sources__tag--warn">1&star;</span>
                  </div>
                  <div class="geo-viz-sources__row geo-viz-sources__row--muted">
                    <span class="geo-viz-sources__ic">yr</span>
                    <span>yourbrand.com</span>
                    <span class="geo-viz-sources__tag">&mdash;</span>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="geo-arg__body">
                <div class="geo-arg__num">04</div>
                <h3 class="geo-arg__title">You're cited &mdash; but not from your site.</h3>
                <p class="geo-arg__copy">Someone else is writing your story. LLMs pull from Reddit threads, review sites, and blog posts &mdash; because your first-party content wasn't set up to be the source of truth.</p>
              </div>
            </article>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
    <!-- 03 · THE COST                               -->
    <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
    <section class="geo-cost">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="geo-cost__inner">
          <span class="geo-eyebrow geo-eyebrow--light">The cost</span>
          <h2 class="geo-cost__title">
            Every &ldquo;didn't get named&rdquo; is a<br />
            <span class="text-gradient">buyer you'll never see.</span>
          </h2>
          <div class="geo-cost__stats">
            <div class="geo-cost__stat">
              <div class="geo-cost__stat-num">60%</div>
              <div class="geo-cost__stat-label">of Google searches now end without a click</div>
            </div>
            <div class="geo-cost__stat">
              <div class="geo-cost__stat-num">700M+</div>
              <div class="geo-cost__stat-label">weekly users on ChatGPT alone</div>
            </div>
            <div class="geo-cost__stat">
              <div class="geo-cost__stat-num">0</div>
              <div class="geo-cost__stat-label">of your competitors are measuring this yet</div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <p class="geo-cost__note">Traditional SEO reports don't show what didn't happen. The mentions you missed don't hit a dashboard. Which is exactly why the window is still open.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
    <!-- 04 · WHAT GEO ACTUALLY IS                   -->
    <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
    <section class="geo-section" id="playbook">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="geo-sheet">
          <div class="geo-intro">
            <span class="geo-eyebrow">The primer</span>
            <h2 class="geo-section__title">GEO isn't SEO with a <span class="text-gradient">new hat</span>.</h2>
            <p class="geo-section__subtitle">Different engines. Different ranking mechanics. Different measurement. Same goal: be the answer.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="geo-compare">
            <div class="geo-compare__col geo-compare__col--old">
              <div class="geo-compare__head">
                <span class="geo-compare__tag">Yesterday</span>
                <h3 class="geo-compare__title">SEO</h3>
                <p class="geo-compare__sub">Rank a page. Earn the click.</p>
              </div>
              <ul class="geo-compare__list">
                <li><span>Optimize for</span><b>Keywords</b></li>
                <li><span>Content shape</span><b>Long-form pages</b></li>
                <li><span>Wins by</span><b>Backlinks + freshness</b></li>
                <li><span>Measured by</span><b>Rank + clicks</b></li>
                <li><span>Reader</span><b>A human</b></li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="geo-compare__col geo-compare__col--new">
              <div class="geo-compare__head">
                <span class="geo-compare__tag geo-compare__tag--new">Today</span>
                <h3 class="geo-compare__title">GEO</h3>
                <p class="geo-compare__sub">Get named in the answer.</p>
              </div>
              <ul class="geo-compare__list">
                <li><span>Optimize for</span><b>Entities + intents</b></li>
                <li><span>Content shape</span><b>Structured Q&amp;A, schema, facts</b></li>
                <li><span>Wins by</span><b>Citations across trusted sources</b></li>
                <li><span>Measured by</span><b>Mentions, share of voice, sentiment</b></li>
                <li><span>Reader</span><b>An LLM &rarr; then a human</b></li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
    <!-- 05 · SERVICES / THE STACK                   -->
    <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
    <section class="geo-section geo-section--services">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="geo-sheet">
          <div class="geo-intro">
            <span class="geo-eyebrow">The stack</span>
            <h2 class="geo-section__title">The full stack that gets you <span class="text-gradient">named</span>.</h2>
            <p class="geo-section__subtitle">Six workstreams, one team, owned end to end. Not a checklist &mdash; a system that compounds.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="geo-services">
            <article class="geo-service">
              <div class="geo-service__num">01</div>
              <h3 class="geo-service__title">AI Visibility Audit</h3>
              <p class="geo-service__copy">Where you appear &mdash; and don't &mdash; across ChatGPT, Perplexity, Claude, Gemini, and Google AI Overviews. Baseline share of voice against your top 5 competitors.</p>
              <ul class="geo-service__list">
                <li>200+ prompt scan across your category</li>
                <li>Named vs. cited vs. missing breakdown</li>
                <li>Competitor citation source map</li>
              </ul>
            </article>

            <article class="geo-service">
              <div class="geo-service__num">02</div>
              <h3 class="geo-service__title">Structured Content Rewrite</h3>
              <p class="geo-service__copy">Product pages, guides, and FAQ rewritten so LLMs can extract, quote, and cite. Facts first, tone second, tokens third.</p>
              <ul class="geo-service__list">
                <li>Answer-first paragraph structure</li>
                <li>Comparison, spec, and pricing blocks</li>
                <li>Prompt-shaped Q&amp;A sections</li>
              </ul>
            </article>

            <article class="geo-service">
              <div class="geo-service__num">03</div>
              <h3 class="geo-service__title">Schema + JSON-LD</h3>
              <p class="geo-service__copy">Product, FAQ, Review, HowTo, Organization &mdash; marked up cleanly so answer engines can understand what you sell and who you are.</p>
              <ul class="geo-service__list">
                <li>Complete Product + Offer coverage</li>
                <li>Aggregate reviews + individual review nodes</li>
                <li>Entity relationships &amp; sameAs graph</li>
              </ul>
            </article>

            <article class="geo-service">
              <div class="geo-service__num">04</div>
              <h3 class="geo-service__title">Digital PR for AI</h3>
              <p class="geo-service__copy">Digital PR reframed for citation, not vanity backlinks. We map where your competitors are cited, then place you on the industry bodies, trade press, review platforms, and category listicles LLMs already trust.</p>
              <ul class="geo-service__list">
                <li>Competitor citation source audits</li>
                <li>Anchor-text strategy (how AI describes you)</li>
                <li>Wikipedia + entity infobox management</li>
              </ul>
            </article>

            <article class="geo-service">
              <div class="geo-service__num">05</div>
              <h3 class="geo-service__title">First-Party Knowledge Base</h3>
              <p class="geo-service__copy">The FAQ, guide, and glossary corpus LLMs prefer over hallucination-prone Reddit threads. When the model needs a source, it finds yours first.</p>
              <ul class="geo-service__list">
                <li>Ingestion-friendly hub architecture</li>
                <li>Prompt-mapped content coverage</li>
                <li>Refresh cadence + freshness signals</li>
              </ul>
            </article>

            <article class="geo-service">
              <div class="geo-service__num">06</div>
              <h3 class="geo-service__title">% of Responses Reporting</h3>
              <p class="geo-service__copy">The dashboard nobody else has. Your headline metric: <b>% of responses</b> you appear in across every engine &mdash; benchmarked against your top 5 competitors, tracked weekly, tied to pipeline.</p>
              <ul class="geo-service__list">
                <li>Weekly automated engine scans</li>
                <li>Competitor share-of-voice tracking</li>
                <li>Attribution for AI-sourced sessions</li>
              </ul>
            </article>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
    <!-- 06 · METHOD                                 -->
    <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
    <section class="geo-method">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="geo-method__inner">
          <div class="geo-intro geo-intro--light">
            <span class="geo-eyebrow geo-eyebrow--light">The method</span>
            <h2 class="geo-section__title">How the engagement runs.</h2>
            <p class="geo-section__subtitle">A 90-day cycle. Then it compounds &mdash; every quarter your citations, structure, and mention share get denser.</p>
          </div>

          <ol class="geo-steps">
            <li class="geo-step">
              <div class="geo-step__num">01</div>
              <div class="geo-step__label">Days 1&ndash;14</div>
              <h3 class="geo-step__title">Baseline</h3>
              <p class="geo-step__copy">200-prompt scan across ChatGPT, Perplexity, Claude, Gemini, and Google AI Overviews. We map exactly where you're named, cited, missing, or misrepresented &mdash; and against whom.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="geo-step">
              <div class="geo-step__num">02</div>
              <div class="geo-step__label">Days 15&ndash;45</div>
              <h3 class="geo-step__title">Rewrite</h3>
              <p class="geo-step__copy">Product pages, guides, and FAQ restructured. Schema + JSON-LD shipped. Your site becomes machine-readable without losing its human voice.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="geo-step">
              <div class="geo-step__num">03</div>
              <div class="geo-step__label">Days 30&ndash;75</div>
              <h3 class="geo-step__title">Seed</h3>
              <p class="geo-step__copy">Entity placements, citation outreach, review-site cleanup, and knowledge-base publish. We plant the sources LLMs will find on their next crawl.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="geo-step">
              <div class="geo-step__num">04</div>
              <div class="geo-step__label">Days 60&ndash;90 &rarr; ongoing</div>
              <h3 class="geo-step__title">Measure</h3>
              <p class="geo-step__copy">Weekly engine scans. Share of voice, sentiment, referral traffic. You see the mentions climb &mdash; and then you see the pipeline follow.</p>
            </li>
          </ol>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
    <!-- 06.5 · PROOF / RESULTS                      -->
    <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
    <section class="geo-section geo-section--proof">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="geo-sheet">
          <div class="geo-intro">
            <span class="geo-eyebrow">The proof</span>
            <h2 class="geo-section__title">What the numbers look like at <span class="text-gradient">30 / 60 / 90</span>.</h2>
            <p class="geo-section__subtitle">Directional benchmarks from category launches. Every brand starts in a different spot &mdash; the trajectory is what matters.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="geo-proof">
            <article class="geo-proof__card">
              <div class="geo-proof__day">Day 30</div>
              <div class="geo-proof__metric">
                <span class="geo-proof__from">&lt;5%</span>
                <span class="geo-proof__arrow">&rarr;</span>
                <span class="geo-proof__to text-gradient">baseline mapped</span>
              </div>
              <h3 class="geo-proof__title">You see the map.</h3>
              <p class="geo-proof__copy">Most brands find they're named in fewer than 5% of buyer-intent prompts on day one. You get a source-by-source breakdown of where competitors are cited, and the exact structural gaps holding you back.</p>
            </article>

            <article class="geo-proof__card geo-proof__card--hero">
              <div class="geo-proof__day">Day 60</div>
              <div class="geo-proof__metric">
                <span class="geo-proof__from">Named</span>
                <span class="geo-proof__arrow">&rarr;</span>
                <span class="geo-proof__to text-gradient">2&ndash;3&times;</span>
              </div>
              <h3 class="geo-proof__title">Structure ships. Mentions climb.</h3>
              <p class="geo-proof__copy">Schema is live. Structured content is indexed. First citations land on trusted sources. Named mentions typically climb 2&ndash;3&times; as engines re-crawl and re-ingest.</p>
            </article>

            <article class="geo-proof__card">
              <div class="geo-proof__day">Day 90</div>
              <div class="geo-proof__metric">
                <span class="geo-proof__from">15&ndash;25%</span>
                <span class="geo-proof__arrow">&rarr;</span>
                <span class="geo-proof__to text-gradient">of responses</span>
              </div>
              <h3 class="geo-proof__title">Category presence.</h3>
              <p class="geo-proof__copy">Compounded citations plus first-party structure land brands in 15&ndash;25% of category prompts. That's the threshold where AI-referral pipeline shows up in analytics.</p>
            </article>
          </div>

          <p class="geo-proof__note">Benchmarks from ecommerce category launches. Categories with heavier incumbents move slower; niche categories move faster. The audit tells you which you're in.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
    <!-- 07 · FAQ                                    -->
    <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
    <section class="geo-section">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="geo-sheet">
          <div class="geo-intro">
            <span class="geo-eyebrow">Questions</span>
            <h2 class="geo-section__title">Answers, in the order you'll <span class="text-gradient">ask them</span>.</h2>
          </div>

          <div class="geo-faq">
            <details class="geo-faq__item">
              <summary>Is GEO just SEO with a rebrand?</summary>
              <p>No. SEO wins the click on a search results page. GEO wins the citation inside an AI-generated answer. Different engines, different signals, different measurement. You need both &mdash; they don't replace each other, they compound.</p>
            </details>
            <details class="geo-faq__item">
              <summary>Do I need to abandon my current SEO work?</summary>
              <p>No. Well-structured SEO content is actually the foundation of good GEO. What we do is layer schema, structured answers, and entity strategy on top &mdash; and rewrite the pages that were built for humans-only so LLMs can also parse them.</p>
            </details>
            <details class="geo-faq__item">
              <summary>How do you measure something you can't rank on?</summary>
              <p>We run weekly automated prompt scans across ChatGPT, Perplexity, Claude, Gemini, and Google AI Overviews &mdash; 200+ buyer-intent prompts specific to your category. You get share of voice, mention count, sentiment, and citation sources. Same rigor as rank tracking, new terrain.</p>
            </details>
            <details class="geo-faq__item">
              <summary>How long until I see results?</summary>
              <p>Schema and structured content changes get picked up in weeks. Citation strategy compounds over 60&ndash;90 days as sources get crawled and re-ingested by model training or retrieval systems. By month three, most engagements see 3&ndash;5x increase in named mentions.</p>
            </details>
            <details class="geo-faq__item">
              <summary>What if my brand isn't the &ldquo;authority&rdquo; in my category?</summary>
              <p>Even better. Category leaders are already cited. The window is wide open for brands two or three spots down &mdash; because most competitors haven't started this yet. The next 12 months decides who owns the answer for the next five.</p>
            </details>
            <details class="geo-faq__item">
              <summary>Do you handle the implementation or just the strategy?</summary>
              <p>Implementation. Same team that runs your storefront runs your GEO. Schema shipped by our devs. Content rewritten by our writers. Citations placed by our team. You don't hand a strategy PDF to another vendor.</p>
            </details>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
    <!-- 08 · CTA                                    -->
    <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
    <section class="geo-cta">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="geo-cta__inner">
          <h2 class="geo-cta__title">
            See exactly what <span class="text-gradient">% of responses</span><br />
            you're already in.
          </h2>
